target.message:
Added PySide support. Moved build process to release-time rather than install-time.
Users may install from pip or easy_install without having PySide or PyQt4 installed.
However if they want to build from a mercurial clone alone, they will need to
have PySide and pyside-rcc, and/or PyQt4 and pyrcc4, whicher they want to use
support for either can be enabled and disabled via boolean flags at the top
of setup.py.

Bumped version to 1.4.0
Bumped minor version number for release
version number now determined from setup.py
Releasing version 1.0.0
modified setup.py to remove unneccessary information

Fixed versioning information so it is only stored in one place.

The setup.py file auto-generates a __version__.py file which is included as part of the distribution.

Fixed a bug whereby qsettings_wrapper didn't work on PyQt4 with v1 APIs.

Bumped patch number for release.

Added auto_scroll_to_end module, with its method set_auto_scroll_to_end

This is a function that takes a scrollbar as an argument, and configures it
to be kept scrolled to the end whenever the range of the scrollbar increases,
but only if it was already scrolled to the end before the range was increased.

This is useful for text output and adding items to a list.

Modified OutputBox to use this instead of duplicating code.

Bumped patch version number.
replaced setattr
All labscript suite icons added, bumped patch version for release
Bumped version for release

Fixed bug where buffering of text to the outputbox was not working.
Messages were being sent individually and it was very slow for certain
kinds of text
Bumped patch number for PyPI release

Merged in cbillington/qtutils (pull request #6)

Allow a zmq Context to be passed into OutputBox.

Approved-by: Philip Starkey <philip.starkey@monash.edu>
Bumped version to 1.6.0 for python 3 support

Ensured QSettingsWrapper setter and getter run in the main thread.
Better install error messages.
Patch bump.
Merge with 1.2.0-dev

Fixed mistake in license which didn't include a reference to the terms in the GPL_EXCEPTION.TXT file in the PyQt project source.

bumped version to v1.2.1
Build process appears to work correctly. Releasing as v1.3.0
remove "rc1" from version for release
Version bump for release candidate
